  "local_port": 59522,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the use of a meta tag in HTML?",
  "response": "Meta tags are HTML elements used to provide metadata about a web page. They are placed in the <head> section of an HTML document and offer various purposes:\n\n1. Page Description\n```html\n<meta name=\"description\" content=\"A brief description of the webpage\">\n```\n- Provides a summary for search engines\n- Often displayed in search results\n\n2. Character Encoding\n```html\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n```\n- Specifies the character encoding for the document\n- Ensures proper text rendering\n\n3. Viewport Configuration\n```html\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n```\n- Controls page scaling and responsiveness\n- Essential for mobile-friendly websites\n\n4. Keywords\n```html\n<meta name=\"keywords\" content=\"HTML, web development, coding\">\n```\n- Indicates relevant keywords for search engines\n- Less important for SEO now\n\n5. Author Information\n```html\n<meta name=\"author\" content=\"John Doe\">\n```\n- Specifies the page's author\n\n6. Robots Instructions\n```html\n<meta name=\"robots\" content=\"index, follow\">\n```\n- Guides search engine crawlers\n- Controls indexing and link following\n\n7. Open Graph Meta Tags\n```html\n<meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"Page Title\">\n```\n- Provides metadata for social media sharing\n\nThese tags help improve SEO, accessibility, and page presentation.",
